{"lemma":"عُمْرَةٌ","slug":"عُمْرَةٌ","root":"ع.م.ر","root_slug":"ع-م-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-م-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عُمْرَة","root":"عمر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30522"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"umrah (a minor hajj, a lesser pilgrimage to Mecca, other than at the time of the hajj)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Classical Syriac ܥܘܡܪܐ (ʕumrɑ(ʔ), “congregation, communion”)."},"ipa":["/ʕum.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30522","headword_ar":"عُمْرَةٌ","root":"Emr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A visit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a visiting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a visit in which is the cultivation"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimaArap","text_ar":"عِمَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of love"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a repairing to an inhabited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a peopled, place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is the primary signification. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-  Hence the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eumorap","text_ar":"عُمْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"in pilgrimage [and at any time]; (S, O; *) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A religious visit to the sacred places at Mekkeh, with the performance of the ceremony of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iHoraAm","text_ar":"الاـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the circuiting round the Kaabeh, and the going to and fro between Es-Safà and El-Marweh:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaj~u","text_ar":"الحَجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[differs from it inasmuch as it is at a particular time of the year and] is not complete without the halting at 'Arafát on the day of 'Arafeh: (Zj, TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eumorap","text_ar":"عُمْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minor pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaj~u","text_ar":"الحَجُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSogaru","text_ar":"الاَصْغَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (Msb, and Kull p. 168;) what is commonly termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaj~u","text_ar":"الحَجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being called sometimes the greater pilgrimage ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaj~u AlA^akobaru","text_ar":"الحَجُّ الاَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (Kull:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumarN","text_ar":"عُمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumaraAtN","text_ar":"عُمَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumuraAtN","text_ar":"عُمُرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumoraAtN","text_ar":"عُمْرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b3-  Also A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going in to his"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"newlymarried"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife in the abode of her family:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K:) if he removes her to his own family, the act is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurosN","text_ar":"عُرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","Zj","Kull","O","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}